{"000-section": {"000-title": "PM Jeeven Jyoti Bima Yojana (PMJJBY) & Craft and Gear Scheme for Fisherman in Goa"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Pradhan Mantri Jeevan Jyoti Bima Yojana for Fishermen", "001-normal": "PM Jeevan Jyoti Bima Yojana is a one year Insurance Scheme being offered by LIC. Any fishermen is now eligible to fill the PMJJBY Application / Claim Form and can get Rs. 2 lakh as compensation amount in case of death of the fishermen.", "002-normal": "However, the candidates must fulfill the eligibility criteria to become eligible to apply for PMJJBY:-  \n **PMJJBY Eligibility Criteria for Fishermen**", "003-listElement": "- This scheme is applicable only for the fishermen who is already engaged in the occupation of fishing and other sea related activities.", "004-listElement": "- All the fishermen between the age of 18 to 50 years can apply.", "005-listElement": "- Applicants must be residing in Goa for the past 15 years or more.", "006-listElement": "- Fishermen must be a member of any of the Fisheries co-operative societies.", "007-listElement": "- Fishermen must submit his good health certificate and a self declaration that he is not suffering from any acute illness.", "008-listElement": "- Moreover all the fishermen must possess an active savings bank account for the auto debit facility of the premium amount.", "009-normal": "The annual premium of PMJJBY stands currently at Rs. 330. Out of this premium amount, 50% (Rs 165) will be borne by the Goa state government while the balance 50% will be borne by Life Insurance Corporation of India (LIC). For more details, please see the \u2013 [Pradhan Mantri Jeevan Jyoti Bima Yojana Guidelines](https://sarkariyojana.com/pradhan-mantri-jeevan-jyoti-bima-yojana-pmjjby/)"}, "002-section": {"000-title": "Craft and Gear Scheme for Fishermen", "001-normal": "The important features of Craft and Gear Scheme for fishermen are as follows:-", "002-listElement": "- All the Traditional and Co-operative fishermen of general category will get 40% subsidy on purchase of craft and gear.", "003-listElement": "- Fishermen from Scheduled Caste (SC), Scheduled Tribes (ST) category and women will get 60% subsidy for craft and gear.", "004-normal": "Both these schemes are for the welfare of fishermen to make them self-reliant and self-dependent to earn their livelihood."}}